    comment: '<p>The default value for <code>box-sizing</code> is <code>content-box</code>. This setting indicates only the content is included in the total <code>width</code> and <code>height</code> properties.</p>\n<p>Using <code>padding-box</code> will include the content and padding, but is only supported in Firefox.</p>\n<p>The most popular value <code>border-box</code> will include content, padding and border. This makes working with percentages and building the layout easier, since the total <code>width</code> and <code>height</code> values include all three properties.</p>\n<p>Both squares are initially defined as <code>250Ã—250</code>. Because of the different <code>box-sizing</code> values, one expands because of the padding, while the other does not:</p>\n<p><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><svg width="100%" height="auto" viewBox="0 0 800 320" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.2" baseProfile="tiny"><desc>Created by HiQPdf</desc><defs></defs><g fill="none" stroke="black" stroke-width="1" fill-rule="evenodd" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="bevel" ><g fill="#596193" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><path vector-effect="none" fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10,0 L808,0 L808,318 L10,318 L10,0"/></g><g fill="#000000" fill-opacity="1" stroke="#000000" stroke-opacity="1" stroke-width="1" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="bevel" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><text fill="#000000" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" xml:space="preserve" x="290" y="138" font-family="Times New Roman" font-size="16" font-weight="400" font-style="normal" > </text></g><g fill="#ffffff" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><path vector-effect="none" fill-rule="evenodd" d="M108,18 L390,18 L390,300 L108,300 L108,18"/></g><g fill="#000000" fill-opacity="1" stroke="none" transform="matrix(1,0,0,1,0,0)"><path vector-effect="none" fill-rule="evenodd" d="M108,1